                  RS
                  ngOnInit firing every time "Shoppping List" link is clicked
                  In this class I tested an approach and it worked but I don't know if it is a good practice.So, I didn't emit the event to update the ingredients array in the "ShoppingListComponent" upon adding ingredients to the shopping list through recipe details.I simply pushed the ingredients to the ingredients array in the "ShoppingListService".What I realized is that every time we click on the "Shopping List" header link, the "ShoppingListComponent" initializes again, firing the ngOnInit method, and thus, updating the ingredients array.For this reason, there's no need to emit the notification when adding ingredients through recipe details.Is that reasonable?
